/#
   A type to describe an institution (party) identified by means of a coding scheme and an optional name.
 #/
record FpML5.reporting.ReferenceBank {
  # An institution (party) identifier, e.g. a bank identifier code (BIC).
  referenceBankId : string?

  # The name of the institution (party). A free format string. FpML does not define usage rules for the element.
  referenceBankName : string?

}

referenceBankId.Doc: An institution (party) identifier, e.g. a bank identifier code (BIC).
referenceBankId.Name: referenceBankId

referenceBankName.Doc: The name of the institution (party). A free format string. FpML does not define usage rules for the element.
referenceBankName.Name: referenceBankName
